  "prompt": "Can allergies cause dizziness and head pressure?",
  "response": "Yes, allergies can potentially cause dizziness and head pressure, although these symptoms are not the most common ones associated with allergic reactions. Allergies can lead to inflammation and congestion in the sinuses, which may result in a feeling of pressure in the head. This sinus congestion can also affect balance and lead to dizziness.\n\nAdditionally, allergies might cause other symptoms like nasal congestion, sneezing, headaches, or fatigue, which could also contribute to feelings of dizziness or head pressure. If you are experiencing these symptoms and are unsure about the cause, it's a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional to determine the underlying reason and appropriate treatment.",
